                          java.util.function.Function<U,java.lang.String> printFunction,
                          java.util.function.BiFunction<U,java.lang.String,java.lang.Boolean> selectFunction)
        Create a GetObjectOfListCmd that will use the given list of users as the options in the select process.
        Parameters:
        listOfObjects - The list of users to pick from. When null is passed an empty list will be used.
        printFunction - The function used to print the objects of the list.
        selectFunction - The function used to filter in the list when the user provides a String input.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If at least one of the functions is null

              DataModel dummy2,

       throws CancelException,

        Create a scenario where the person will choose an Object from the list passed to the constructor. Uses both functions passed to the constructor to print the options and filter the answers. Prints 'No options found.' and returns null when the list is empty.
        Specified by:
        exec in interface Cmd<U>
        Parameters:
        scan - Used to interact with the person who selects the option.
        dummy2 - Dummy
        dummy3 - Dummy
        Returns:
        The selected option, can be null if the list of options was empty.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the given scan is null
        CancelException - When the person has indicated to abort the cmd.
